blic schools and draconian limitations on union bargaining rights. It includes a detailed account of the actual bargaining process revealing the mundane and the transcendental strategies of both school board and union representatives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aEducation and statezIllinoiszChicago. 0aStrikes and lockoutsxTeacherszIllinoiszChicago. 0aTeachersxPolitical activityzIllinoiszChicago. 4aEducation & History Of Education. 4aLabor History. 4aU.S. History.  aPublic education, labor relations, school systems, educational governance, school board, union representatives.1 aBruno, Robert, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066749340uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150170593940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501705939423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501705939/original  a978-3-11-066749-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles